<title type="html"><![CDATA[Any mapper 0 game(s) that used Save-RAM ($6000-7FFF)?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6378&amp;p=61251#p61251"><![CDATA[
I don't think any comercial roms used that space.<br />But I once hacked an FDS game to be mapper #0 with SRAM.  Just stuck a small loader on to copy the appropriate area to SRAM, then jump into the game.  (I also used simple RLE to make it a tad smaller so the loader would fit.)<br />Some emulators refused to run it (mapper #0 isn't supposed to have sram), others ran it fine.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=53">Dwedit</a> — Mon May 10, 2010 12:52 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
